# 🔐 Authentication API Documentation

## 📌 Overview

This module handles:

* User login
* Password change (first login or manual)

Authentication is based on **JWT (JSON Web Token)**.

**Base URL:**

```
http://localhost:5000
```

All routes are prefixed with:

```
/auth
```

---

# 🔑 1. Login

## 🔗 Endpoint

```
POST /auth/login
```

---

## 📥 Request Body

```json
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "YourPassword123"
}
```

---

## ✅ Success Response

```json
{
  "message": "Login successful",
  "token": "JWT_TOKEN_HERE",
  "roles": ["student", "admin"],
  "must_change_password": true
}
```

---

## ❌ Error Responses

```json
{ "error": "Email and password are required" }
{ "error": "Invalid credentials" }
{ "error": "Wrong password, try again" }
```

---

# 🔐 2. Change Password

## 🔗 Endpoint

```
POST /auth/change-password
```

---

## 🔐 Headers (REQUIRED)

```
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
```

⚠️ Must include the word **Bearer**

---

## 📥 Request Body

```json
{
  "new_password": "NewPassword123",
  "confirm_password": "NewPassword123"
}
```

---

## ✅ Success Response

```json
{
  "message": "Password changed successfully",
  "token": "NEW_JWT_TOKEN"
}
```

👉 Replace the old token with the new one.

---

## ❌ Error Responses

```json
{ "error": "Both password fields are required" }
{ "error": "Passwords do not match" }
{ "error": "Password must be at least 8 characters" }
{ "error": "Password must contain at least one uppercase letter" }
{ "error": "Password must contain at least one number" }
{ "error": "New password must differ from your current password" }
{ "error": "Unauthorized" }
```

---

# 🔄 Authentication Flow

## 🪜 Step-by-step

### 1. User logs in

* Call `/auth/login`
* Store:

  * token
  * roles
  * must_change_password

---

### 2. Check password requirement

```js
if (data.must_change_password) {
  window.location.href = "/change-password";
}
```

---

### 3. User changes password

* Call `/auth/change-password`
* Replace old token with new token

---

### 4. Access protected routes

Include token in every request:

```js
headers: {
  Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`
}
```

---

# 💻 Frontend Examples

## Login Example

```js
const res = await fetch("/auth/login", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    email: "user@example.com",
    password: "Password123"
  })
});

const data = await res.json();

localStorage.setItem("token", data.token);

if (data.must_change_password) {
  window.location.href = "/change-password";
}
```

---

## Change Password Example

```js
const token = localStorage.getItem("token");

const res = await fetch("/auth/change-password", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    new_password: "NewPassword123",
    confirm_password: "NewPassword123"
  })
});

const data = await res.json();

// update token after password change
localStorage.setItem("token", data.token);
```

---

# 🔐 Token Details

* Type: JWT
* Expiration: **8 hours**
* Contains:

  * user id
  * email
  * roles
  * must_change_password

---

# ⚠️ Security Notes

## 🔴 Token Expiration

* User must re-login after 8 hours

---

## 🔴 Best Practices

* Do NOT store passwords
* Prefer HttpOnly cookies over localStorage (production)
* Always send token in Authorization header
* Use HTTPS in production

---

# 📌 Summary

| Feature         | Endpoint                   | Auth Required |
| --------------- | -------------------------- | ------------- |
| Login           | POST /auth/login           | ❌             |
| Change Password | POST /auth/change-password | ✅             |

---

# 📌 Notes for Frontend

* Store JWT token after login
* Handle `must_change_password`
* Replace token after password change
* Attach token to all protected requests
* Handle token expiration (redirect to login)

